flow.description: This flow creates a new bucket using nifi-toolkit-cli commands to create a bucket versioned in git and allows the user to add flows to it from the nifi-ui without restarting all systems.
flow.name: NewGitBucket

Permit Whitespace and Comments in Patter.displayName: Permit Whitespace and Comments in Pattern
Permit Whitespace and Comments in Patter.name: Permit Whitespace and Comments in Pattern

Enable Literal Parsing of the Pattern.displayName: Enable Literal Parsing of the Pattern
Enable Literal Parsing of the Pattern.name: Enable Literal Parsing of the Pattern

properties.Command Arguments: -c "/c/Users/Dafni/Documents/Apache_Nifi/nifi-toolkit-2.2.0/bin/cli.sh registry create-flow -u http://localhost:18080 -b ${bucketId} -fn ${flowName} -fd 'delete once real flow is imported'"

Permit Whitespace and Comments in Patter.displayName: Permit Whitespace and Comments in Pattern
Permit Whitespace and Comments in Patter.name: Permit Whitespace and Comments in Pattern

Enable Literal Parsing of the Pattern.name: Enable Literal Parsing of the Pattern

properties.Command Arguments: -c "cd /c/Users/Dafni/Documents/Apache_Nifi/nifi-registry-2.2.0/git-flow-storage && git add . && git commit -m 'Adding snapshot for ${bucketName}'"

properties.bucketDesc: Flow allows user to automate the creation of a dummy bucket using nifi-toolkit-cli commands in order that they can actively select the newly created bucket to start version control on processor group and changes are committed to git repo
